# Local-only OOM frontier finder for sweep_wanda.py.
#
# Algorithm (per-host (batch_size, max_seq_len) OOM probe):
#   * For each batch_size row, binary-search seq_len for the largest passing
#     value — O(log n_seq) cells per row instead of O(n_seq).
#   * Monotonicity propagation across the grid:
#       (b, s) ok   => (b' <= b, s' <= s) ok
#       (b, s) oom  => (b' >= b, s' >= s) oom
#     Inferred cells are not retested.
#   * Rows are dispatched across _AVAILABLE_DEVICES in parallel via a
#     ThreadPoolExecutor; a shared `known` dict + lock lets siblings prune
#     cells already proven by other workers.
#   * `run_fn` shells out to `conda run … sweep_wanda.py … --device cuda:N`
#     and classifies stdout/stderr as ok / oom / err via OOM_MARKERS.
#     Injectable so the search logic can be unit-tested without a GPU.
#
# Scratch only — not part of the baseline sweep. Re-create from git history
# if you ever need it again.
_grid_oom.py
_test_grid_oom.py
